        </p>
        <blockquote> Instructional split attention occurs when learners are
          required to split their attention between and mentally integrate
          several sources of physically or temporally disparate information,
          where each source of information is essential for understanding the
          material. Cognitive load is increased by the need to mentally
          integrate the multiple sources of information. This increase in
