        before the child makes an attempt.&nbsp; This is an illustration of
        temporal or time separation.&nbsp; The child has to remember the entire
        process before being able to make an attempt.&nbsp; To illustrate a
        spatial one, we need only look at an <br>
        ordinary math book.&nbsp; <br>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Math books often combine a text based explanation
        with an equation, chart, or diagram that are separated on the page
        spatially, which means that the explanation is on one part of the page
        while the equation or diagram is on another part of the page. <br>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Usually, the text appears first with a parenthetical
        reference to the equation, such as (See Fig. 4-5).&nbsp; <br>
        I noticed the split�attention effect while I was taking a statistics
